This paper deals with relay assisted transmission in multiuser networks, which involves information theory (IT) and network infrastructure (NI). The paper also discusses interference and capacity regions, which are topics in signal processing (SI) and communication engineering (CE). Additionally, the paper considers the use of codebooks, which is a common technique in multimedia (MM) applications. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IT and cs.NI, followed by cs.SI, cs.MM, and cs.CE.
